The paper deals with the management of information updates in a communication system, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The use of queuing theory to model the source-destination link suggests that the paper could also be classified under networked systems (cs.NI) or control systems (cs.SY). The analysis of packet management schemes and the computation of average age and peak age of information could be relevant to performance evaluation (cs.PF) or mathematical analysis (cs.MA) of communication systems.
